    <div class="container">
      <header>
        <h1>Understanding Media Queries</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">
          Resize your browser to see responsive design in action
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="content">
        <div class="box explanation">
          <h2>What are Media Queries?</h2>
          <p>
            Media queries are a CSS technique that allows you to apply styles
            based on device characteristics such as:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Screen width and height</li>
            <li>Device orientation (portrait/landscape)</li>
            <li>Resolution and pixel density</li>
            <li>Preferred color scheme (dark/light mode)</li>
            <li>Reduced motion preferences</li>
            <li>Print media</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            They are essential for creating responsive websites that work on all
            devices.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="box">
          <h2>Common Breakpoints</h2>
          <p>
            While these can vary based on your content, common breakpoints are:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Mobile:</strong> 0px - 767px</li>
            <li><strong>Tablet:</strong> 768px - 1023px</li>
            <li><strong>Desktop:</strong> 1024px - 1199px</li>
            <li><strong>Large Desktop:</strong> 1200px+</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Always test your design at multiple sizes rather than relying
            strictly on these numbers.
          </p>
          <hr />
          <div class="element">Actual Content</div>
        </div>

        <div class="box code-example">
          <h2>Media Query Syntax</h2>
          <pre><code>/* Mobile-first approach */
.element {
  width: 100%;
  padding: 1rem; 
}

/* Tablet styles (768px and up) */
@media (min-width: 768px) {
  .element {
    width: 50%;
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }
}

/* Desktop styles (1024px and up) */
@media (min-width: 1024px) {
  .element {
    width: 33.33%;
    padding: 2rem;
  }
}

/* Dark mode support */
@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
  body {
    background-color: #1a202c;
    color: #e2e8f0;
  }
}

/* Print styles */
@media print {
  .no-print {
    display: none;
  }
  
  body {
    font-size: 12pt;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
}

/* Reduced motion */
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  * {
    animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
  }
}</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>

      <footer>
        <p class="footer-text">
          Try resizing your browser, printing this page, or enabling dark mode
          to see media queries in action!
        </p>
      </footer>
    </div>

    <script>
      // Add current window width display for educational purposes
      document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", function () {
        const header = document.querySelector("header");
        const widthDisplay = document.createElement("div");
        widthDisplay.style.marginTop = "20px";
        widthDisplay.style.padding = "10px";
        widthDisplay.style.background = "rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1)";
        widthDisplay.style.borderRadius = "5px";
        widthDisplay.style.fontWeight = "bold";
        widthDisplay.style.color = "#4a5568";

        function updateWidthDisplay() {
          widthDisplay.textContent = `Current viewport width: ${window.innerWidth}px`;
        }

        updateWidthDisplay();
        header.appendChild(widthDisplay);

        window.addEventListener("resize", updateWidthDisplay);
      });
    </script>
